OL,6,FHe set out for the Government to
OL,7,Fconsider a new offence where an
OL,8,Findividual with an intention of
OL,9,Fkilling two or more people engages
OL,10,Fwith any preparation to carry out that
OL,11,Fintention.
OL,13,FHe recommended the maximum sentence to
OL,14,Fbe life imprisonment.
OL,16,FSouthport MP Patrick Hurley however,
OL,17,Fsays he "respectfully disagrees" with
OL,18,Fthe watchdog findings and that what
OL,19,Fhappened in Southport was "clearly
OL,20,Fterroristic" which needs a "common
OL,21,Fsense approach" in the definition.
